<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Flat List Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>A heat map is a graphical representation of data where values given by a variable in a two-dimensional map are represented by colors. This sample demonstrates how flat list items are bound to the HeatMap control.</Paragraph><Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
<Image Source="Images\Flat List Demo.png" Height="520" Width="750" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Supports the <Bold>Intersect</Bold> action to avoid overlapping of text.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>


<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The <Bold>Text Intersect Action</Bold> drop-down is used to set the Intersect action for the heat map item text.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The slider <Bold>"Select Median Weight"</Bold>allows changing the interior of a heatmap item. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>


<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The slider <Bold>"Border thickness of HeatMap Items"</Bold> helps change the border thickness of a heatmap item. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>


<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The button <Bold>"Add New Item"</Bold> will add a new heatmap item.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
</List>
</FlowDocument>